<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="87" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[746,1396,522,1268]" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">
Suffrutescent plant 50–70 cm high. Stem densely hairy. Lamina of the leaves elliptic, coriaceous, 2.5–4 × 1.3–2 cm, cuneate to subrounded at the base, obtuse at the tip, with up to 5 lateral ascendent nerves, glabrous to sparsely hairy above, silky-villous below, sessile or subsessile; bracts three or four times narrower than the leaves; calyx lobes elliptic, papery, entire, densely silky, posterior and anterior one about 2.3 × 1.2 cm, lateral ones lanceolate, 1.5 cm long; corolla 3 cm long, glandular outside, without upper lobes and with three orbicular-obovate lower lobes 15 × 16 mm and with a cylindrical tube 15 mm long, 3–4 mm wide at the throat. Stamens not seen at anthesis, anthers 4 mm long in bud; style about 25 mm long. Capsule black, ellipsoid-oblong, 27 mm long and 10 mm wide, apparently 2-seeded (
<emphasis box="[1122,1233,1079,1103]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">Desenfans</emphasis>
663). 
<figureCitation box="[1302,1365,1079,1103]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[56,124,1901,1923]" captionTargetBox="[233,1209,196,1765]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[137,1316,168,1846]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1 – Barleria velutina (A–D) and B. obtecta (E–G). Barleria velutina: A, habit; B, posticous calyx lobe; C, lateral calyx lobe; D, onelipped corolla. Barleria obtecta: E, leaf; F, posticous calyx lobe; G, lateral calyx lobe (A–D, Schmitz 7698; E–G, Desenfans 676)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1486152/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="87">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
